
[1]copula

   COPULA, n. [L. See Copulation and Couple.] In logic, the word which
   unties the subject and predicate of a proposition. Religion is
   indispensable to happiness. Here is is the copula joining religion, the
   subject, with indispensable to happiness, the predicate.
